Rosneft, Severstal, Evraz, Polyus Gold: Russian Equity Preview

-- B y   I l y a   A r k h i p o v
-- 
2011-05-16T20:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-16/rosneft-severstal-evraz-polyus-gold-russian-equity-preview.html
The following companies may be active
in Russian trading in Moscow. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are from the previous close of trading.  Russia ’s 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  fell 0.6 percent to 1,622.98.
The dollar-denominated RTS Index dropped 1.1 percent to
1,846.32.  OAO Rosneft (ROSN RX): BP Plc is likely to miss a second
deadline for a share swap with OAO Rosneft after failing to
agree to a buy-out of its partners in Russia’s third-largest oil
producer in time, said people with knowledge of the plans.
Rosneft, Russia’s largest oil producer, gained 0.1 percent to
230.57 rubles.  OAO Severstal (CHMF RX): Russia’s largest steelmaker is
expected to release first-quarter results. Severstal fell 0.5
percent to 466.50 rubles.  Evraz Group SA (EVR)  : Russia’s second-biggest steelmaker
is expected to report first-quarter financial highlights.
Company global depositary receipts rose 0.3 percent to $32.04 in
 London .  OAO Polyus Gold (PLZL RX): Russia’s biggest gold producer
and KazakhGold Group Ltd reached an agreement with AltynGroup
Kazakhstan LLP. According to the AltynGroup’s statement, it
resulted in “full and final settlement of all claims and
litigation between the parties.” Polyus gained 0.1 percent to
1,903.70 rubles on the Micex.  To contact the reporter on this story:
